cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about language modeling using neural networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the advantages of distributed representations and long-range contexts in neural language models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new architecture for LSTM nodes, which is a type of artificial neural network.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper focuses on recurrent neural networks and their application to language modeling.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the advantages of LSTM architecture in modeling long-range contexts, which is also relevant in computer vision tasks.
